                                                                                                               SBI profit jumps 42%
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                          Great going                                  
	Mumbai, July 30: The State Bank of India has reported a 42 per cent increase in net profit at Rs 2,330.37 crore in the first quarter ended June 30, buoyed by a robust growth in treasury income.        
	The bank had reported a net profit of Rs 1,640.79 crore in the same quarter a year ago.        
	Indias No. 1 lender had an income stream of close to Rs 6,385.43 crore from trading in bonds, up from Rs 4,328.90 crore in the year-ago period.        
	Net interest income  the difference between interest earned from loans and that paid on deposits  grew only 4.30 per cent to Rs 5,025 crore.        
	With non-interest income rising to Rs 3,569 crore (Rs 2,404 crore) largely because of a strong growth in both core fee income and forex income, and interest on balances with the Reserve Bank of India also showing good growth, the total income of the bank stood at Rs 21,041.51 crore against Rs 16,203.07 crore a year ago.        
	Deposits grew to Rs 7,63,563 crore during the period from Rs 5,61,857 crore a year earlier. The current and savings account ratio as on June 30 stood at 38.45 per cent. The banks market share in deposits was 17.55 per cent, up from a little over 15 per cent last year.        
	Gross advances rose Rs 1,02,046 crore to Rs 5,49,793 crore from Rs 4,47,747 crore a year ago. While advances to large firms grew 37 per cent, that to mid-level companies rose 15 per cent.        
	Advances to SMEs increased 24 per cent. Home loans grew 24.03 per cent and auto loans, 29.05 per cent. The banks balance sheet size increased to Rs 9,76,989 crore from Rs 7,45,367 a year ago.        
	Gross non-performing assets went up to Rs 15,318.29 crore (Rs 10,827.81 crore). After provisioning, net NPAs rose to Rs 8,402.48 crore (Rs 6,298.44 crore). The bank said it restructured Rs 8,118 crore of loans during the quarter against Rs 10,951 crore pending for the period.                                                                                                                                                     
